# CSS & BEM (`cl-`)

## Pattern

`.cl-block-name__element-name_modifier-name_modifier-value`

- Lowercase Latin; words separated by **hyphens**.
- Block ↔ element: **`__`**; modifiers: **`_`** (omit value for boolean modifiers).

## Implementation rules

- One scoped **`Component.css`** per component; **no hard-coded** colors/spacing when a variable exists.
- Use **`var(--cl-*)`** from `src/main.css` (e.g. `--cl-base-font-color`, `--cl-m-gap`, `--cl-accent-a0`, `--cl-border-radius`).
- Theme: variables switch for light default and **dark** when `.cl-components-dark-theme` is active (see `main.css` / Storybook).

```css
.cl-widget {
  color: var(--cl-base-font-color);
  padding: var(--cl-m-gap);
  border-radius: var(--cl-border-radius);
}
.cl-widget__label { display: flex; gap: var(--cl-s-gap); }
.cl-widget_disabled { opacity: 0.5; cursor: not-allowed; }
```

Compose class names in TSX with **`getClassName`**, not string concatenation for conditionals.
